      <Expense>3415259</Expense>
      <Description>The HOPE Center Distribution Program: The HOPE Center provided a week of groceries for 100,351 individuals struggling to feed their families in 2010. Of the 100,351 individuals served, 41,592 were children. One out of four children suffer from hunger in the Dallas/FW Area Many of these people are without jobs, others disabled and many seniors. Some families support children whose parents are in prison. Each family is qualified by the TEXCAP eligibility guidelines of the State of Texas to determine their income level. We provided emergency food four days a week in Tarrant and Dallas Counties by partnering with Central Dallas Ministries and Abundant Life Church in Dallas, with distribution from The HOPE Center in Fort Worth. We also distribute Clothes each week to assist individuals needing clothes for employment or other needs. Also childrens school clothes and school supplies are distributed. During the Christmas Holiday, we have a large Toy distribution for children who have been registered to families who receive food.</Description>
      <Activity2>
        <Expense>4587</Expense>
        <Description>The School of HOPE was birthed to "Feed HOPE" in the lives of individuals seeking employment. Since 2007 we have had tremendous growth not only in students but also in classes offered. In East Fort Worth over 50% of the high school students are drop outs. We offer Pre-GED and GED Programs to help students get back on track and to either go on to college or qualify for more job opportunities. For those seeking computer skills, we offer Keyboard 101 and Microsoft Office Suite. For employment in warehouses, we offer Forklift and Scissor Lift certification. Over 150 student have received employment through our certification programs.</Description>
      </Activity2>
      <Activity3>
        <Description>In 2008 The Hope Center initiated The KEYS of HOPE, an after school and summer program for children to learn how to play the keyboard and sing in a choir. They performed throughout the community. In 2010, The Keys of HOPE partnered with Children of Glory School of Fine Arts, to expand our music training. The School of Fine Arts met at The HOPE Center and is a DBA under the covering of The HOPE Center. We continue to have after school and summer training, but it has been expanded to include not only music lessons in keyboard, voice and choir, but also dance. Performances are done on a regular basis in churches in the community.</Description>
      </Activity3>
      <ActivityOther>
        <Description>Program services expenses support the distribution of food and goods to the needy and partnering organizations. These include expenses for delivery vehicles, forklifts, warehouse utilities, personnel and repairs. There are currently over 500 active volunteers who assist in The HOPE Center's activities.</Description>
      </ActivityOther>
